examples.remarks: Remove the website data for $bucket.

parameters.description: The name of the bucket to configure. This parameter will also accept a Bucket object.
parameters.name: Name

parameters.description: Storage object for the "main page" of the website, e.g. what is served from "http://example.com/". Defaults to "index.html".
parameters.name: MainPageSuffix

parameters.description: Storage object to render when no appropriate file is found, e.g. what is served from "http://example.com/sadjkffasugmd". Defaults to "404.html".
parameters.name: NotFoundPage

cmdlets.description: Updates the website associated with a Cloud Storage Bucket.
cmdlets.synopsis: Updates the website associated with a Cloud Storage Bucket.
cmdlets.name: Write-GcsBucketWebsite

remarks: Host http://example.com from the contents of $bucket.
Next, set the domains DNS records to point to Cloud Storage. See the "Static WebsiteHosting" help topic for more information.
